    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 2",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "I have seen Him in the watchfires of a hundred circling camps;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 7
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "They have builded Him an altar in the evening dews and damps;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 10
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 55
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "I can read His righteous sentence by the dim and flaring lamps;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 6
      }, {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 41
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 57
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "His day is marching on.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 20
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 3",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "He has sounded forth the trumpet that shall never sound retreat;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 7
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "He is sifting out the hearts of men before His judgment seat;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 6
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 56
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "O be swift, my soul, to answer Him !",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 5
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "be jubilant, my feet !",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 3
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 16
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "Our God is marching on.",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "A",
        "position" : 4
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 20
      } ]
    } ]
  }, {
    "type" : "verse",
    "label" : "Verse 4",
    "lines" : [ {
      "text" : "In the beauty of the lilies Christ was born across the sea,",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 7
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "With a glory in His bosom that transfigures you and me;",
      "chords" : [ {
        "chord" : "G",
        "position" : 7
      }, {
        "chord" : "D",
        "position" : 52
      } ]
    }, {
      "text" : "As He died to make men holy, let us die to make men free;",
      "chords" : [ {
